content: I've seen a few birds at the feeder, including some that I'm pretty sure are Northern Cardinals and Blue Jays. There was one bird that I'm not sure about - it was medium-sized, had a black back and white belly, and a red cap on its head. I'm not sure what that one is. As for the hike, I didn't notice any birds that I didn't recognize, but I was mostly focused on the trails and the scenery.
